article.headline: Utah 73, Air Force 65
article.story:
AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. (AP) -- Carley Marshall had a game-high
21 points to lead No. 25 Utah over Air Force 73-65 Saturday.

Kim Smith added 14 points for the Utes, and Kelsey Stireman had
11. Utah (20-5, 10-1 Mountain Western Conference) has never lost to
Air Force (3-20, 0-10), winning all 15 matchups.

Still, the Falcons scored the most points ever against their
conference foe. Air Force's previous average score against Utah has
been 39 points.

Letricia Castillo led the Falcons with 14 points, the 14th time
the freshman guard has been the team's top scorer. Amoy Jackson
contributed 10 points and eight rebounds.

After falling behind early, Air Force made 3-pointers on five of
six trips down the court to take a 17-15 lead. Utah then went on an
11-0 run to jump ahead by nine points.

By the break, the Utes increased their lead to 39-21.

Air Force cut a 20-point deficit to eight in the final six
minutes, but couldn't close the gap further. The Falcons shot 39.3
percent (24-of-61) from the field. Utah made 50 percent (23-of-46).
